703944f-a.text:
Debevoise Ave., at the N.E. corner of Maspeth Ave. These homes facing on Maspeth Ave., housed the employees of Peter Cooper, who conducted a glue factory in the rear of these houses. (Cooper Park and Cooper Union were
named in his memory.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

705606f-a.text:
(1).  125-137 Maspeth Ave., north side, between Debevoise and Morgan Aves., showing a row of old frame houses. (This land was owned by Peter Cooper in 1855).
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, a northeasterly view.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, showing houses built by Peter Cooper for his workmen now opposite Cooper Park. (He operated a glue factory, which was
situated behind these houses).
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4)
The same, another view.
September 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
